Building the openframe project wrapper:

	cd sg13cmos5l_ocd_openframe

If nix is not installed, then follow instructions from
	https://librelane.readthedocs.io/en/sttable/installation/\
	nix_installation/installation_linux.html

This will start the nix-daemon.  If librelane is not installed, then
clone it from https://github.com/librelane/librelane

Start the nix shell by cd'ing to the librelane repository root and doing:

	nix-shell

Once in the nix shell, cd back to the design repository (e.g.,
sg13cmos5l_ocd_openframe/librelane/, where this README is located), and do:

	export PDK_ROOT=<where the ihp-sg13cmos5l PDK is located>

	librelane config.yaml --manual-pdk --pdk ihp-sg13cmos5l --pdk-root ${PDK_ROOT}

NOTE:  The run results are *not* pushed back to the git repository, because
the size of everything in the directories is huge.  The project final output
was copied into the ../gds/ directory, and the project can be recreated on
demand from the existing configuration files.
